text: It seems obvious that if an expedition to Brittany was compelled to attack via Calais, then the primary essential to the success of the French war was a navy in unquestioned command of the Channel. It seems obvious that divided forces were dissipating the advantages of a of bridge-heads which included Calais, Cherbourg, Brest, Bordeaux and Bayonne, and that there was no hope of final victory without a large-scale and concentrated invasion
